ğŸ“Œ GATE asks to apply, not prove

ğŸ”¹ Common GATE Traps

Euler â†’ count degrees

Hamilton â†’ check structure

Euler conditions are necessary & sufficient

Hamilton conditions are only sufficient

2ï¸âƒ£ Practice: 30 GATE-Level MCQs
Q1.

Euler path uses every edge:
Answer: Exactly once
Explanation: Definition.

Q2.

Euler circuit must start and end at:
Answer: Same vertex
Explanation: Closed path.

Q3.

In Euler path, vertices may repeat?
Answer: Yes
Explanation: Edges are restricted, not vertices.

Q4.

In Hamilton path, vertices may repeat?
Answer: No
Explanation: Each vertex exactly once.

Q5.

Euler path depends on:
Answer: Degrees of vertices
Explanation: Odd/even degree rule.

Q6.

Hamilton path depends on:
Answer: Graph structure
Explanation: No simple formula.

Q7.

An undirected graph has Euler circuit if:
Answer: All vertices have even degree
Explanation: Necessary & sufficient.

Q8.

An undirected graph has Euler path (not circuit) if:
Answer: Exactly two vertices have odd degree
Explanation: Start and end vertices.

Q9.

Graph with 4 odd-degree vertices has Euler path?
Answer: No
Explanation: More than 2 odd vertices.

Q10.

Graph with 0 odd-degree vertices has:
Answer: Euler circuit
Explanation: All even.

Q11.

Directed Euler circuit requires:
Answer: in-degree = out-degree for all
Explanation: Balance condition.

Q12.

Directed Euler path requires:
Answer: One start, one end imbalance
Explanation: +1 and âˆ’1 condition.

Q13.

Hamiltonian circuit covers:
Answer: All vertices once
Explanation: Definition.

Q14.

Which graph is always Hamiltonian?
Answer: Complete graph
Explanation: Easy to find cycle.

Q15.

Which graph is always Eulerian?
Answer: Cycle graph
Explanation: All degrees = 2.

Q16.

Tree can have Euler circuit?
Answer: No
Explanation: Leaves have degree 1.

Q17.

Tree can have Euler path?
Answer: Only if exactly two vertices exist
Explanation: Degree-1 leaves.

Q18.

Path graph has Euler path?
Answer: Yes
Explanation: Two odd vertices.

Q19.

Path graph has Hamilton path?
Answer: Yes
Explanation: Visits all vertices once.

Q20.

Diracâ€™s theorem applies for n â‰¥ ?
Answer: 3
Explanation: Condition requirement.

Q21.

Diracâ€™s theorem condition:
Answer: deg(v) â‰¥ n/2
Explanation: For all vertices.

Q22.

Oreâ€™s theorem condition:
Answer: deg(u)+deg(v) â‰¥ n
Explanation: Non-adjacent vertices.

Q23.

Diracâ€™s theorem guarantees:
Answer: Hamiltonian graph
Explanation: Sufficient condition.

Q24.

Euler theorem gives:
Answer: Necessary & sufficient condition
Explanation: Complete test.

Q25.

Hamiltonian theorems are:
Answer: Sufficient only
Explanation: Not necessary.

Q26.

Most PYQ-tested Euler concept?
Answer: Counting odd-degree vertices
Explanation: Always asked.

Q27.

Most PYQ-tested Hamilton concept?
Answer: Dirac/Ore application
Explanation: Standard GATE questions.

Q28.

Euler path ignores:
Answer: Vertex repetition
Explanation: Allowed.

Q29.

Hamilton path ignores:
Answer: Edge repetition
Explanation: Edge reuse allowed.

Q30.

Biggest GATE trap here?
Answer: Mixing Euler & Hamilton conditions
Explanation: Very common error.
